one another: a comedy of manners written by a fine poet, or a satirical poem in the genre of Pushkin's "Gavriliad", may have its "lewd" side; but LOLITA is a tragedy. Pornography is not an image plucked out of context. Pornography is an attitude and an intention. The tragic and the obscene exclude one another.

I don't say anything about PNIN but may have something to tell about him another time.





As ever,

Vladimir Nabokov





TO: JASON EPSTEIN

CC, 1 p.





Mt. Carmel, Utah

May 25, 1956